ms%20Department%20and%20Network%20Systems%20Department.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fchina%2Fchina-pla-undergoes-major-restructure-as-it-emphasises-information-capabilities-for-war%2Farticleshow%2F109713814.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia-indiatimes-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fchina%2Fchina-pla-undergoes-major-restructure-as-it-emphasises-information-capabilities-for-war%2Famp_articleshow%2F109713814.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fchina%2Fchina-pla-undergoes-major-restructure-as-it-emphasises-information-capabilities-for-war%2Famp_articleshow%2F109713814.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22What%20Is%20TTS%2C%20A%20Rare%20Condition%20Caused%20By%20AstraZeneca's%20Covishield%20Vaccine%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAstraZeneca%2C%20a%20British%20pharmaceutical%20giant%2C%20has%20admitted%20that%20its%20Covid-19%20vaccine%20can%20result%20in%C2%A0%3Ca%20data-mce-href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fin-big-u-turn-astrazeneca-admits-its-covishield-vaccine-can-cause-side-effect-5553754%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fin-big-u-turn-astrazeneca-admits-its-covishield-vaccine-can-cause-side-effect-5553754%5C%22%3Ea%20rare%20side%20effect%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0known%20as%20Thrombosis%20with%20Thrombocytopenia%20Syndrome%20(TTS).%C2%A0This%20acknowledgement%20follows%20a%20lawsuit%20filed%20against%20the%20company%2C%20alleging%20serious%20harm%20and%20deaths%20linked%20to%20the%20vaccine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20court%20documents%2C%20Covishield%2C%20a%20vaccine%20developed%20by%20AstraZeneca%20and%20Oxford%20University%20and%20manufactured%20by%20the%20Serum%20Institute%20of%20India%2C%20can%2C%20in%20rare%20instances%2C%20lead%20to%20this%20condition.%20This%20vaccine%20was%20extensively%20administered%20throughout%20India%20during%20the%20Covid-19%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EWhat%20is%20Thrombosis%20with%20Thrombocytopenia%20Syndrome%20(TTS)%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThrombosis%20with%20Thrombocytopenia%20Syndrome%20(TTS)%20is%20a%20rare%20condition%20in%20which%20blood%20clots%20form%20in%20unusual%20places%20in%20the%20body%2C%20and%20the%20number%20of%20platelets%20in%20the%20blood%20drops.%20Platelets%20are%20small%20cells%20that%20help%20blood%20to%20clot%2C%20so%20having%20too%20few%20of%20them%20can%20be%20dangerous.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20condition%20was%20observed%20in%20people%20who%20received%20adenoviral%20vector%20COVID-19%20vaccines%2C%20such%20as%20Vaxzevria%2C%20Covishield%20(AstraZeneca)%20and%20the%20Johnson%20%26amp%3B%20Johnson%2FJanssen%20COVID-19%20vaccine.%20TTS%20seems%20to%20occur%20because%20the%20body's%20immune%20system%20reacts%20to%20the%20vaccine%20by%20making%20antibodies%20that%20attack%20a%20protein%20involved%20in%20blood%20clotting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETTS%20is%20classified%20into%202%20tiers%20by%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmvec.mcri.edu.au%2Freferences%2Fthrombosis-with-thrombocytopenia-syndrome%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DWhat%2520is%2520TTS%253F%2C4%252D42%2520days%2520after%2520vaccination.%C2%A0%5C%22%3ECDC%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3ETier%201%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%20data-mce-style%3D%5C%22font-weight%3A%20400%3B%5C%22%3ERare%20blood%20clots%2C%20like%20in%20the%20brain%20or%20gut%2C%20sometimes%20alongside%20more%20typical%20ones%20in%20the%20legs%20or%20lungs.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%20data-mce-style%3D%5C%22font-weight%3A%20400%3B%5C%22%3ELow%20platelet%20count%20(below%20150%2C000%20per%20microliter).%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%20data-mce-style%3D%5C%22font-weight%3A%20400%3B%5C%22%3EPositive%20anti-PF4%20ELISA%20tests%20can%20help%20confirm%20diagnosis%20but%20aren't%20always%20needed.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%20data-mce-style%3D%5C%22font-weight%3A%20400%3B%5C%22%3ETier%201%20cases%20are%20usually%20more%20severe%20and%20riskier.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%20data-mce-style%3D%5C%22font-weight%3A%20400%3B%5C%22%3EThis%20is%20more%20common%20in%20younger%20people.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3ETier%202%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%20data-mce-style%3D%5C%22font-weight%3A%20400%3B%5C%22%3ECommon%20blood%20clots%2C%20like%20in%20the%20legs%20or%20lungs.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%20data-mce-style%3D%5C%22font-weight%3A%20400%3B%5C%22%3ELow%20platelet%20count%20(below%20150%2C000%20per%20microliter).%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%20data-mce-style%3D%5C%22font-weight%3A%20400%3B%5C%22%3EA%20positive%20anti-PF4%20ELISA%20test%20is%20necessary%20for%20diagnosis.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3ETTS%3A%20Symptoms%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESymptoms%20of%20TTS%20can%20include%20severe%20headaches%2C%20stomach%20pain%2C%20swelling%20in%20the%20legs%2C%20trouble%20breathing%2C%20and%20problems%20with%20thinking%20or%20seizures.%20If%20someone%20shows%20these%20signs%20after%20getting%20a%20vaccine%2C%20they%20should%20see%20a%20doctor%20right%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1714453980000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2021-12%2F9fh3h5is_covishield-covid-vaccine-pti_625x300_27_December_21.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwhat-is-tts-a-rare-condition-caused-by-astrazenecas-covishield-vaccine-5554568%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22AstraZeneca%2C%20a%20British%20pharmaceutical%20giant%2C%20has%20admitted%20that%20its%20Covid-19%20vaccine%20can%20result%20ina%20rare%20side%20effectknown%20as%20Thrombosis%20with%20Thrombocytopenia%20Syndrome%20(TTS).T%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwhat-is-tts-a-rare-condition-caused-by-astrazenecas-covishield-vaccine-5554568%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwhat-is-tts-a-rare-condition-caused-by-astrazenecas-covishield-vaccine-5554568%2Fam